{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13206: [custom elements api] using v-if in custom element slot doesn't work",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:00.302750+00:00",
  "text": "[custom elements api] using v-if in custom element slot doesn't work\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClick on the button multiple times and see no `<div v-if=\"count >` content\n\n### What is expected?\n\nWhen we click on the button third time both `Count > 1 using v-if condition` and `Count > 1 using v-show condition` should be visible when isShown true and count is more that 1.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\ncontent from <div v-if> never shows\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\npossibly related to this issue https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/13199",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug",
    "scope: custom elements"
  ],
